Devlicio.us Launched!

Posted by Brendan Tompkins on September 20, 2006

For the past few months, I've been working on a new  blogging site for .NET developers.  At Devlicio.us, I'm going to try to employ some of the same techniques that we've used here at CodeBetter.Com to help us become successful, like recruiting seasoned, smart bloggers, providing branding promotion and advertisement, and hopefully crafting a mainfeed with a small number of quality posts designed to be read in a sitting. 

CodeBetter.Com has over 9,000 Bloglines Subs 

It's a strategy that's worked for us here at CodeBetter, in fact, today we're celebrating over 9,000 Bloglines Subscriptions!  That puts us ahead of CNET, Scripting News and USA Today's Technology feed.  In fact, CodeBetter.Com's mainfeed is amongst the top 100 blogs, according to Bloglines.

Devlicio.us is Recruiting!

It's been hard deciding when to launch, but I've gone ahead and opened Devlicio.us' doors, even though you won't find a ton of posts there.  I have lined up a few bloggers who are getting ready to post, but my #1 priority is to sign up some great blogs.

So, if you're 1) a .NET blogger looking for a new home, and a chance to get new readership, or 2) a seasoned .NET developer looking to start a blog or 3) know anyone who falls into category 1 or 2, get in touch with me at brendan.tompkins@gmail.com.  

Thanks and be sure to check us out!
